#### Cookie Preference Center

  * Your Privacy
  * Critical Cookies
  * Performance Cookies
  * Tracking Cookies

##### Your Privacy

Our website places small files called "cookies" on your browser that provides
our team information that helps us provide a better experience to our site
users. We label these cookies in three ways: Critical, Performance, and
Tracking. You can find descriptions for each type by clicking the tabs on the
left.

##### Critical Cookies

These cookies are critical for the site to function and cannot be switched off
in our systems. These cookies also track anonymous data which is used to help
us better understand how our users interact with our site to provide a better
user experience.

##### Cookies used

Google Analytics and Tag Manager

We track anonymous data to better understand how our visitors interact with
our website. This includes information such as what is clicked, how much time
is spent on the site and how you reached us.

Content Management System

These are cookies needed by our content management to function correctly.

Hubspot

These cookies allow us to track anonymous data to better understand how our
visitors interact with our website.

__hs_do_not_track, __hssc, __hssrc, __ptq.gif, __hstc, hsfirstvisit,
hubspotutk | Until performance cookies are set, these cookies allow us to
track strictly anonymous data  
---|---  
  
EqualWeb

This code is used to add a web accessibility feature to the website and does
not extract data from the website.

##### Performance Cookies

Inactive

These cookies are set through our site by our marketing partners. They allow
us to tie your support calls and form responses back to your visit to ensure
the website offered you the best possible experience in getting the
information you needed.

##### Cookies used

Hubspot

These cookies allow us to track your behaviour on our site.

__hssc |  
---|---  
__hssrc | "Keeps track of a visitor's identity. This cookie is passed to the
marketing platform HubSpot on form submission and used when de-duplicating
contacts."  
__ptq.gif | "Sends data to the marketing platform Hubspot about the visitor's
device and behaviour. Tracks the visitor across devices and marketing
channels."  
__hstc | The main cookie for tracking visitors. It contains the domain, utk
(see below), initial timestamp (first visit), last timestamp (last visit),
current timestamp (this visit), and session number (increments for each
subsequent session).  
hsfirstvisit | Cookie is used to determine if you have previously accessed the
site.  
hubspotutk | This cookie is used for to keep track of a visitor's identity.
This cookie is passed to HubSpot on form submission and used when de-
duplicating contacts.  
  
##### Tracking Cookies

Inactive

These cookies are set through our site by our analytic and marketing partners.
They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests so we
can provide the best possible user experience for you through our website and
marketing campaigns. They work by uniquely identifying your browser, operating
system, IP and location.

##### Cookies used

Facebook Pixel

Used by Facebook for marketing purposes.

Google Tag Manager

By default, our tag manager code is set up to track page views using the
Google's IP Anonymization feature turned on. Also, all the cookies that are
set up from Google by default, are set up to expire after the browsing session
ends. Turning on this cookie type, will tell Google that the full IP can be
used to track your behavior on our website.

_tgmanonymous | If set to 1, will tell google that it can track the full IP
and it will set up it's cookies to expire in 365 days, not 0 days as set up by
default.  
---|---
